RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s ambassador to Mexico, Haytham bin Hassan Al-Malki, presented his credentials as a nonresident ambassador to El Salvador’s President Nayib Bukele.
Al-Maliki conveyed the greetings of King Salman and Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman to Bukele, wishing El Salvador and its people further progress and prosperity, the Saudi Press Agency reported on Friday.
Bukele wished the Saudi leadership and people the same, as well as wishing Al-Malki success in his duties.